                <h1>Understanding Background Meaning in Art</h1>
                <p>In art, background refers to the part of a composition that supports the main subject. It creates context, depth, and mood, influencing how viewers interpret the focal point. A well-crafted background can enhance the narrative and emotional impact of the artwork, guiding the observer's eye and enriching the overall experience.</p>
